\cf3 2.3 Consensus Mechanisms (Proof of Work, Proof of Stake)\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Introduction\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Consensus mechanisms are crucial components of blockchain networks, ensuring agreement on the state of the ledger across all participants. We'll focus on two primary mechanisms: Proof of Work (PoW) and Proof of Stake (PoS).\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 What is a Consensus Mechanism?\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 A method for validating transactions and creating new blocks\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Ensures all nodes in the network agree on the current state of the blockchain\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Prevents double-spending and maintains the integrity of the network\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Proof of Work (PoW)\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Definition:\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 A consensus mechanism that requires solving complex mathematical puzzles to validate transactions and create new blocks\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 How PoW Works:\cf2 \
\cf3 1. Miners compete to solve a cryptographic puzzle\cf2 \
\cf3 2. First miner to solve the puzzle gets to add the next block\cf2 \
\cf3 3. Other nodes verify the solution\cf2 \
\cf3 4. If valid, the new block is added to the blockchain\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Advantages of PoW:\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Highly secure against attacks\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Proven track record (used by Bitcoin)\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Disadvantages of PoW:\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Energy-intensive\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Potential for mining centralization\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Slower transaction processing\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Examples of PoW Cryptocurrencies:\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Bitcoin\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Litecoin\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Dogecoin\cf2 \
