\cf3 2.4 Smart Contracts\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Introduction\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Smart contracts are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement directly written into code. They are a key feature of many blockchain platforms, enabling automated, trustless transactions and complex decentralised applications.\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Definition of Smart Contracts\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Computer programs stored on a blockchain\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Automatically execute when predetermined conditions are met\cf2 \
\cf3 \'95 Enforce the terms of an agreement without the need for intermediaries\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Key Characteristics of Smart Contracts\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 1. Autonomy\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Execute automatically without intervention\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 2. Decentralisation\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Exist on a distributed blockchain network\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 3. Transparency\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 All parties can view the contract's code and execution\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 4. Immutability\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Once deployed, the code cannot be changed\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 5. Deterministic\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Produce the same result for everyone who runs them\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 How Smart Contracts Work\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 1. Creation\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Developer writes the contract code, defining conditions and actions\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 2. Deployment\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Contract is uploaded to the blockchain\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 3. Execution\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Contract self-executes when predefined conditions are met\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 4. Verification\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Network nodes verify the execution\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 5. Update of Blockchain State\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Results of the contract execution are recorded on the blockchain\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Advantages of Smart Contracts\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 1. Efficiency\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Automate processes, reducing time and cost\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 2. Accuracy\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Eliminate errors from manual filling of documents\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 3. Trust\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Remove the need for intermediaries\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 4. Transparency\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 All parties can view and verify the contract\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 5. Security\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Encrypted and distributed across the network\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 Limitations and Challenges\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
\cf3 1. Code Vulnerabilities\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\'a0 \'95 Bugs in the code can lead to unintended consequences\cf2 \
\cf3 \'a0\cf2 \
